basics.summary:
I am a Software Engineer experienced but not limited to Python, with skills on the full stack & machine learning. Coding commercial Python for more than 17 years, right after leading my infra team to create a XEN cloud. When allowed, am used to design, build, and maintain highly reliable systems that scale to millions of requests per second (RPS).
&nbsp;
 Now I do what gets needed from cloud-or-not DevOps to intermediate HTML/CSS/JS, mainly using Postgres+Redis and Django or Flask or FastAPI on the backend. Usualy with queue-driven and event-driven async designs. Also worked with machine learning and published a paper at an international academic conference.
&nbsp;
I try to proactively collaborate my bugfixes to opensource initiatives when possible. This way I contributed to many projects like Celery, Cassandra, Ansible, DRF, Kivy & RustPython among others, and created the `drf-nested-router` package used by more than 2000 projects including Mozilla Addons server and OpenCVE.
